{{Infobox Online music service | service_name = Ambling Books | opened = 2009 | pricing = Free and paid downloads | platforms = [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[iPhone]], [[iPad]], [[iPod Touch]], [[Windows]], [[macOS]], [[Linux]] | format = [[MP3]] | catalogue = 10,725 audio book titles | protocol = Hypertext Transfer Protocol ([[http]]://) | availability = worldwide | features = Free and discounted audio book downloads; book player software; bookmarking; wireless distribution, wishlist | homepage = AmblingBooks.com | users = 33,739 registered | downloads = 550,093 }}
'''Ambling Books''' was a privately held online company that offered free and paid [[Digital rights management|DRM]]-free [[audiobook]]s for download and audio book player software for computers and mobile devices. Ambling was also a distribution channel for audiobook publishers. The company went out of business in February 2016.<ref name=oob/>
== History == * Nov. 2008 - iBookTreasures.com begins development phase.<ref>{{cite web|title=WHOIS Results for ibooktreasures.com|url=http://www.networksolutions.com/whois-search/ibooktreasures.com|publisher=Network Solutions}}</ref> * Feb. 2009 - Company is incorporated by owner Howard Davis as iBookTreasures, LLC<ref>{{cite web|title=iBookTreasures, LLC|url=https://secure.utah.gov/bes/details.html?entity=7256039-0160 |publisher=Utah Division of Corporations}}</ref> * July 2010 - Launched AmblingBooks.com as a distribution channel for audiobooks.{{Better source|reason=Citation is from the company sponsored press-release; there must be more objective sources for this.|date=October 2018}} * Jan 2011 - Release Ambling BookPlayer for Windows.{{Better source|reason=Citation is from the company sponsored press-release; there must be more objective sources for this.|date=October 2018}} * Mar. 2011 - Released Ambling BookPlayer for the Mac.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ambling Books Software Publisher Profile|url=http://download.cnet.com/mac/ambling-books/3260-20_4-10121209.html|publisher=CNet}}</ref> * July 2011 - Released Ambling BookPlayer for the iPhone, iPad, and iPod Touch<ref>{{cite web|title=Ambling BookPlayer Pro 1.07 for iPhone - Easy, Premium AudioBook Player|url=http://www.iphonelife.com/promotions/ambling-bookplayer-pro-107-iphone-easy-premium-audiobook-player|publisher=iPhoneLife Magazine}}</ref> * February 2016 - Ambling Books shuts down<ref name=oob>http://us4.campaign-archive1.com/?u=cf0a9cb5b739dfcc6761ac4fe&id=bdbdb4b01d </ref>
== Websites == === AmblingBooks.com === In July 2010, Ambling Audio Books launched AmblingBooks.com as a "publisher-friendly" distribution channel for audio book publishers.{{Better source|reason=Citation is from the company sponsored press-release; there must be more objective sources for this.|date=October 2018}} Website offered access to over 10,000 free and discounted audio books from publishers including [[Simon & Schuster]], [[Blackstone Audio]], [[BBC Audiobooks]], [[Tantor Audio]], and [[LibriVox]].
=== AmblingBookPlayer.com === In August 2009, the AmblingBookPlayer.com site was launched offering specialized [[audiobook]] playing software called the Ambling BookPlayer.<ref>{{cite web|title=WHOIS Results for amblingbookplayer.com|url=http://www.networksolutions.com/whois-search/amblingbookplayer.com|publisher=Network Solutions}}</ref> This software, initially created for Android devices, offered several benefits over existing MP3 players: * Automatic file handling (listeners interact with multiple MP3 files as a single book). * Chapter-based, instead of file-based navigation. * Extensive bookmarking and note-making capabilities. * Series-based library organization (titles in a series are ordered by chronological date, not alphabetically). * Automatic bookmark history prevents listeners from losing their place * Sleep timer stops the audio book playback during nighttime listening<ref>{{cite web|title=Ambling BookPlayer Pro Android App Review|url=http://www.androidappdictions.com/archives/1508|publisher=Android App Dictations|access-date=2012-05-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120429040316/http://www.androidappdictions.com/archives/1508|archive-date=2012-04-29|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=AppGuide - Ambling BookPlayer Pro|url=http://www.pcworld.com/appguide/app.html?id=449915|publisher=PCWorld}}</ref> The Ambling BookPlayer application supports both wired and wireless downloading of audio books from AmblingBooks.com.
The Ambling BookPlayer has received high ratings from users of the application.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ambling BookPlayer Pro|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.amblingbooks.bookplayerpro|publisher=Google play}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Ambling BookPlayer Pro|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/ambling-bookplayer-pro/id435659951|publisher=Apple iTunes Preview}}</ref>
